A repository is just a project folder.

  It is the place where GitHub keeps all the files for one project.

    Example:

    my-map-project/
      src/
      package.json
      README.md

That whole folder is the repository.

  Simple meaning:

    A repository is your project’s home.



It holds things like:

  Your code

  Your images

  Your notes

  Your settings

  Your README


Think of it like this:

  Repository = project folder
  GitHub = online place that stores that folder
  Git = tool that tracks changes inside that folder

So when someone says:

  “Push your code to the repo”


They mean:

  “Upload your project changes to the project folder on GitHub.”
